<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-205-116  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 205 116.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  April 10 1989 n533 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A computer virus epidemic.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Computer Virus Industry Association (CVIA) reports aphenomenal growth in the numbers of computer viruses and infectedmachines in 1988, but several national agencies are developingresponses to the situation.andP;  The CVIA estimates the reportednumber of infected computers increased from 3,000 systems in thefirst two months of 1988 to 30,000 in the last two months of theyear.andP;  Strains of computer viruses grew from seven in Feb 1988 to30 by the end of the year.andP;  The National Institute of Standard andTechnology is creating a group to oversee anti-virus responsecenters to be set up by the National Science Foundation, theDepartment of Energy and NASA.andP;  The Defense Advanced ResearchProjects Agency will set up its own response center.andP;  Congresswill consider criminal penalties in the proposed Computer VirusEradication Act.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer Virus Industry AssociationComputer VirusesTrendsImpact AnalysisGovernment Regulation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>